In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine green beans, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a splash of water; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully drain any excess water.

While green beans cook, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat and cover if steak starts to brown too quickly.

Reduce heat to medium low. Stir green beans, scallion whites, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/3%cup}, and @butter{1%tbsp} into pan with steak. Cook, stirring, until butter melts and steak is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If you like a brothier sauce, add splashes of water.

Remove from heat; stir in juice from half the lemon. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Season with salt and pepper if desired.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{}; thinly slice across the grain.

Divide rice and green beans with broth between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Top green beans with steak. Sprinkle with scallion greens, @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.